parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission, specifically the 2nd gear slipping, can cause the motorcycle to lose power, lurch, or jerk, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The motorcycle jumps out of 2nd gear into neutral
and may cause the rear wheel to lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the motorcycle to lose power, lurch, or jerk, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: causing the motorcycle to lose power or jerk violently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose rear brake rotor can cause the brake to malfunction, leading to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The rear brake rotor is loose and can be moved front to back
the rear brake rotor is very loose and almost falls off
the transmission slips when riding in second gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak from the air breather can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: fuel pouring from under the air breather
fuel dripping onto the engine and ground
large puddle of fuel forming on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
